\series bold
Definition 3.12: 
\series default
a series 
\begin_inset Formula $\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}a_{n}$
\end_inset

 is called conditionally convergent if the series 
\begin_inset Formula $\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}a_{n}$
\end_inset

 is convergent but the series of absolute values 
\begin_inset Formula $\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\left|a_{n}\right|$
\end_inset

 is divergent.
\end_layout

