\begin_inset Formula $\left|x-a\right|<R$
\end_inset

, 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote
Then 
\begin_inset Formula $c_{n}=\frac{f^{\left(n\right)}\left(a\right)}{n!}$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(n\right)$
\end_inset

 represent the number of 
\begin_inset Formula $'$
\end_inset

 (or level of derivative)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Taylor Series (Intro)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus, we have a power series representation for the function 
\begin_inset Formula $f\left(x\right)$
\end_inset

 about 
\begin_inset Formula $x=a$
\end_inset

